Definition: inclined or showing an inclination to dispute or disagree, even to engage in law suits
Example: a style described as abrasive and contentious; a disputatious lawyer; a litigious and acrimonious spirit
Synonyms: noun, communication, contention, attribute, contentiousness, combative, disputatious, dispute, act, disputative, verb, litigious, litigiousness, inclined, or, showing, an, inclination, to, disagree, even, engage, in, law, suits, a, style, described, as, abrasive, and, lawyer, acrimonious, spirit
Category: adj.all
